The metagit project can be used to manage a huge amount of git
repositories at one. For example clone all your github Repositories to
a folder on your new shinny machine. The Project is inspired by a article in 
the german LinuxMagazin 08/10 by mschilli.

The configuration is located in the main python skript `metagit'. Edit
it so make it fit your needs. For more information on commands try
`pydoc gmp' to the python module documentation.

A example session:

$ metagit list metagit
+ git@github.com:stettberger/metagit.git --> /home/stettberger/github/metagit

$ metagit foreach metagit commit -a
cd /home/stettberger/github/metagit; git commit  -a
[master d6cb963] removed metagit on peer
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

$ metagit push metagit
[... push ...]

